HEADWORD: Homogenetic
<hw>Ho`mo*ge*net"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Homogenous; -- applied to that class of homologies which arise from
similarity of structure, and which are taken as evidences of common
ancestry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>homogenize</ent>⟦br⟧
